&lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; will bloom again ( italian : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; i &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 2014 italian anti-war film written and directed by ermanno olmi . set in the trenches of the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; plateau , during world war i , it is loosely based on the short story la paura ( 1921 ) , by federico de roberto . it was screened in the berlinale special section at the 65th berlin international film festival . the film received eight nominations at the 2015 david di donatello awards , including best film and best director .